The article discusses an order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to fly the flag of the United States at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of gun violence in Highland Park, Illinois, on July 4, 2022. The order applies to the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and other government facilities in the District of Columbia, as well as the United States embassies, consular offices, and military facilities abroad. The flag will be flown at half-staff until sunset on July 9, 2022. The order was issued on July 5, 2022.